Frugalware 0.3-x86_64 released
Wed Oct 19 19:06:30 CEST 2005
IroNiQ
</p><div align="left">We are pleased to announce the immediate availability of the x86_64 port of Frugalware 0.3.
Frugalware 0.3-x86_64 is now a full-featured port of Frugalware, with almost all of the packages that are available on i686.
What does not work currently?
	<ul><li>OpenOffice.org
	</li><li>Official flash plugin (from Macromedia)
	</li><li>Dosemu</li></ul>
If you can, please test it. If you find a bug, report to <a href="http://bugs.frugalware.org">us</a>. Please include as many details as possible in the bugreport! Thank you.
<b>Important:</b> You will need an AMD64 CPU to use 0.3-x86_64! (Intel processors with EM64T extensions might work as well, but those are untested.)<p>
