KDE 3.4.0 packages are on mirrors
Sun Mar 20 23:30:16 CET 2005
aThom
</p><div align="left">KDE 3.4.0 packages are ready!
You can read the announcement <a href="http://kde.org/announcements/announce-3.4.php">here</a>.
You can read about the new features <a href="http://developer.kde.org/development-versions/kde-3.4-features.html">here</a>.
Packaging changes since 3.3.2:
<ul><li>Changing groups: If you want to install only the core kde packages, use 'pacman -S kde-core', if you want additional packages (k3b, krusader, etc) use 'pacman -S kde'.
</li><li>kde-i18n packages are in the 'extra/locale' group.</li></ul>
New packages:<blockquote>kde-i18n-br, kde-i18n-fy, kde-i18n-ga, kde-i18n-lt, kde-i18n-mk, kde-i18n-se</blockquote>
Removed packages:<blockquote>kde-i18n-af, kde-i18n-el, kde-i18n-fa, kde-i18n-gl, kde-i18n-hr, kde-i18n-mn, kde-i18n-ms, kde-i18n-uz, kde-i18n-zh_TW</blockquote>
Known "bugs" / need to fix:
<ul><li>A bug was found in the groupware support of kontact/kmail, which was too late for the KDE 3.4 release. Get <a href="http://download.kde.org/stable/3.4/src/kdepim-fix-imap-resource-type.diff">kdepim-fix-imap-resource-type.diff</a> applied to the sources before you're using the groupware wizard. For more information, see <a href="http://kde.org/info/3.4.php">http://kde.org/info/3.4.php</a>
</li><li>If you start the OpenOffice.org, and choose File -&gt; Open, then the dialog appears shortly. After that the KDE Crashmanager come up with the following message:
The Program Openoffice (kdefilepicker) crash and send signal 11
It's fixed in the OOo2 KDE builds. (See <a href="http://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=100849">http://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=100849</a>.) As workaround on KDE side, add the following lines to your ~/.kde/share/config/kdeglobals:
[Development]
AutoCheckAccelerators=false
</li><li>Upgraders: after the usual 'pacman -Syu', use 'pacman -S kdelibs kdebase' again, otherwise you'll have problems with kde menus!
</ul></div><p>

